transcript.text: Welcome to On Print Shop.
We have released version 6.2 for On Print Shop and we will see today the features and benefits for B2B printers in version 6.2.

B2B storefront features sub domain provision for corporate storefront, corporate wise theme, corporate level text exempt, pay on limit for corporate user, auto invoice generation and pay on balance Reset Login by username.
First announcement for corporate or B2B is sub domain provision for corporate storefront.
To get the sub domain for a corporate store, you'll need to send an e-mail to a technical team and our technical team will do the required changes.
Formerly what was happening, I'll show an example.
The corporate storefront URL used to be first the domain name, then corporate and then corporate name.
Now you can set a domain name or a corporatename.domainname.com.
So here is an example of how earlier it was working and how it can work now.
So earlier it was like say domainname.com/corporate/corporate name.
Now it can be corporatename.domain.com or directly corporatename.com.
So this is the major enhancement.
Now let's see our next enhancement.
Next enhancement is corporate wise theme.
You can change corporate wise theme.
But for that first you will need to send an e-mail on supported on printshop.com to our technical team as it's a add on as we provide single theme.

And after sending your e-mail or technical team will do the necessary changes and once they do the required changes, you just go to admin panel corporate management, corporates, click on action button and select personalized store.
Under personalized you can go to theme configuration.
And here under select theme you can select a different theme or a particular theme for a particular corporate.

One more thing that you can also personalize the corporate theme by the corporate theme configuration over here you can select standard or you can select custom theme and you can choose the color like red and blue or pink and grey or blue and green.
And also you can set the brand colors individually over here.
So this is our enhancement for corporate theme and corporate store personalization.
Then our next announcement is corporate level tax exempt.
So let's see in the corporate regarding the corporate level text exam.
So to allow corporate level tax exempt go to admin panel, Corporate management, corporates action Edit under settings over here you have an option to allow tax exemption.
So if you want to allow tax exemption for this particular corporate then just simply activate this button and click on save.
So this is how you can give tax exemption to a particular corporate that is corporate wise tax exemption or next enhancement for B2B is pay on limit for corporate users.
So now you can allow pay on limit to a particular customer of a corporate instead of defining the pay on limit for corporate wise or department wise.
So for that just go to admin panel, corporate management, corporates action edit and under settings you can see the pay on account.
So from here you select customer wise and you can set the pay on limit for customers of the particular corporate.
After that we have an enhancement Auto invoice generation and pay on balance reset.
So for auto invoice generation and pay on balance reset, you will need to send an e-mail to our technical team.
They will make the required changes and after that you can follow the path Admin panel, Corporate management, Corporates Action Invoice.
So under invoice go to Invoice settings.
In the invoice settings, first of all enable auto invoice generation.
If you want to enable auto invoice generation, you can set default beyond limit over here date consideration.
So you can select the date consideration for invoice regeneration like say order date or ship date then invoice generation.
You can select when the invoice should be generated monthly or weekly then invoice date you can select from here on which date invoice should be generated and invoice due days.
You can select from here like 15304560 or 90 and you can reset beyond limit over here.
Activate this button to reset the beyond limit and you can reset the beyond limit from here and you can select from here generate invoice for department or corporates that you can select from here.
So this is how you can have the add on of auto invoice generation and beyond balance reset.
So our last announcement to B2B in version 6.2 is login by username.
So next enhancement is login by username.
It enables the end user to login to the system using the username.
So at the time of registration.
Let's take an example of this particular corporate storefront.
You can see over here.
At the time of registration the customer has option to add username.
So at the time of registration when customer adds a username over here, he will be able to login by using the username.
Formerly what was happening that user need to add the e-mail ID instead of username.
So now they can login by using the username.
And if you want this, it's an add on for that you will need to send an e-mail to our technical team on supported on printshop.com and they will activate it for you in your B2B module.
So these are the enhancement we have for B2B module in version 6.2 of on Print Shop.
Thank you for watching this video.

namedLocations.name: ZIP Code
namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

namedLocations.name: ReCAPTCHA
namedLocations.description: reCAPTCHA is a CAPTCHA-like system designed to establish that a computer user is human (normally in order to protect websites from bots) and, at the same time, assist in the digitisation of books. The reCAPTCHA service supplies subscribing websites with images of words that are hard to read for optical character recognition (OCR) software.
